metadata.name: Unicorn #9409
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #8
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Over the Air #60
metadata.description:
During the last couple of decades, over the air television signals and antennas switched to digital, bringing with them a new form of static and distortion as the signal is broken up. "Over the Air" is inspired by these digital distortions, incorporating aspects of them into the same grid-like structure seen on the television. Additional patterns are combined in the grid with these distortions to create the final artwork.

Patterns for the individual blocks in the grid are divided into categories, and various amounts are picked for each work, with dozens of possible mixtures. Patterns can flow in different directions across the varied canvases. Distribution of these patterns across the grid varies from work to work, providing for different feels as they bunch together or spread apart.

metadata.name: Whisper #295
metadata.description:
Abstract forms built with noise and texture

-------------

A note on rendering times: *Whisper has a lot going on*. It can take up to 1-5 minutes to fully render, depending on your hardware configuration, including a 15sec-1min loading phase during which lots of calculations take place (but no visuals). It'll get there, just be patient! A small loading bar along the bottom also shows the progression of the render during the drawing phase.

Press 'S' or click "Save image" to save a PNG version of the artwork while in full-screen/IPFS view

Customisation
-------------

The following parameters can be adjusted in full-screen mode.
Open the token in full-screen/IPFS mode, and add any of these to the URL:

&size=2000 (replace 2000 with any value up to around 8000) - this sets the resolution/width of the canvas in pixels. Use this to generate very large PNG images (50MB+) suitable for printing at large DPI & canvas sizes. The max value here is dependent on your hardware, might not work on mobiles etc.

&ratio=1.4 (any value between 1 and 2, default = 1.4) - set the aspect ratio of the work. By default Whisper renders at 1:1.4 but you can change this to match other printing formats. Different ratios will produce slightly different outputs, but the overall character of the artwork should still be present. Landscape mode is not supported.

metadata.name: Lost Twins #276
metadata.description:
Individually, the mints of this token are very simple. Each mint generates half of two cube forms, and each half is assigned random hues (in multiples of 10, from 0 to 360). Collectively as a project, this token challenges the approach of looking for "rarities" in a new way. How the cubes are rendered leaves the possibility for multiple mints to potentially join up on the sides with colors that perfect match each other. Will you find your lost twin?

Made in p5js
Created November 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Chop Chop #12
metadata.description:
Chop Chop is a complementary collection to Caterpillars that I prepared to thank my collectors for the amazing love and interest you showed to my work. I did not want to force my way to your wallets with unsolicited thank-you nfts, so all holders of Caterpillars will have a reserve spot to mint at least 1 tokens per wallet for 0 tez ( I dont understand the reserve options fully, sorry - 128 editions reserved for holders of Caterpillars) . 

The holders of this collection will have reserve spots for my next  collection. The reserve spots will be held for one week from minting, and I prefer the unreserved editions to be fair game for anyone, so first come, first served.

I decided to re-work this older project of mine because it was going to take some time for me to prepare an independent and novel collection and also wanted to continue learning new things. The concept is Paul Klee meets Vector Math and Flow Fields, as you can see the visuals are heavily inspired by Paul Klee's work :)

Under the hood, the circles and triangles act as repulsive forces that break and distort the grid, and push the squares in their range out of their way, forming some holes in the fabric created by the same algo that made Caterpillars. 

I have only added one rarity feature which is the palette because this one uses almost all the palettes from Caterpillars (minus neon dreams). I am hoping that this project will not be about rarity, but more like a thank-you gift and an easy way to access my future work.

Well, I hope you will like it...

- Press "s" to save a png.

- Also, 33% royalty split wth the Processing Foundation, % 33 with the minters (if there will be any secondary sales) 

DISCLAIMER :
I am very very new to coding and not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside.
